n><hr size=1> I know Cobee tried to start this up but is there any interest in actually doing it?  Lets get a discussion going to see if we can do it.<br><br>Badoo <br>58 Wiz<br>Heroes <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udrunkkeith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>drunkkeith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orc Pawn</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/29/01 3:35:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1046.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Well, It could work under a few suggestions here, first of all is that you properly break into fear and clear those gay west wall roamers first before starting your ae group. if you go in as one or two groups.. peoples zone times vary, and it could get ugly if you have all casters zoning in at different times. If you break it right tho with a good group or two for around 15 mins or so to clear the roamers, I see no reason why this wouldnt work.. for the most part the normal mobs are pretty weak, and if you have the west wall roamers cleared, if you wipeout you should be able to zone right back in without any problems to rez up. My personal suggested fear ae group would consist of 58+ cleric, 60 chanter, 55+ monk, two 58+ wizzies, and 58+ mage.  Gonna need that monk to get the trains pulled in case the golems are up so you have someome to eat the DT and not affect the outcome of the battle, and the fd would be useful in case you agro mini bosses in your train pull.  The biggest problem I forsee with doing this though is when the chanter uses his aoe stuns, I dont care who you are sooner or later your going to have a couple resist that stun, then they start beating on the chanter, interrupting his next aoe stun cast.. then all the stuns wear off and you have a dead chanter. Best solution to this tho would be to hit your aoe stun cycle, then try to get a lvl 60 aoe tash off on yourself.. dunno tho somthing worth looking into. I wouldnt mind trying this someday tho, if you ever get the balls up to give this a shot look me up.. <br><br>Redphoenix Mindmelter<br>60 Phantasmist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubadoo11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Badoo11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/30/01 2:08:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1046.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Good points Red.  I was thinking of more than one group tho.  If we had like 4 chanters all the mobs should stay stunned.  Then a bunch of wizards/mages/and even druids to nuke the heck out of them.  Bards and/or monks could handle the pulling.  Three or four groups would make quick work of the regular mobs leaving plenty of time to kill the boss mobs.<br><br>Badoo<br>58 wiz<br>Heroes <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzarindantarga.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarin Dantarga</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://siyni.homestead.com/files/Pics/thiefwin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ghetto Assassin</span><br>  Posts: 1156<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/30/01 11:19:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1046.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE Fear</span><hr size=1> I thought all Fear raids were AoE.  What have you all been doing? <p><P><table border="0">  <tr>    <td>      <p><font face="verdana, arial" size="-1"><a href= http://www.legacyofsorrow.net/profiles/siyni_prof.html><FONT SIZE=-1><FONT COLOR="Black"><b>Siyni</b></a> <a href=http://www.legacyofsorrow.net><FONT SIZE=-2><FONT COLOR="Black">[ Legacy of Sorrow ]</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14121><FONT SIZE=-4><FONT COLOR="Black"><i>Magelo Profile</i></a></font></td>  </table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiberar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iberar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Megalomaniac</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/30/01 12:34:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1046.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  teehee</span><hr size=1>    Hehe, most fear raids pull 1-3 at a time have chanters mez the rest and kill the mobs one at a time. I'm no PoF expert but when you have a full scale raid on it (30 people) there's no reason NOT to do AOE groups. Pull up 10-15mobs, have everyone bunched up real tight, and launch AOE. Theres quite a few druids/wizards who come on PoF raids. Mages also can AOE *duh* and in the meantime you have your chanters AOE stun. The Mobs only have 10-15k HP if that. Just my 2 cps.<br><br>Iberar Megalomaniac<br>56th Season Arch-Magus<br>Colleague of Sanctuary<br>Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaezon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aezon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Aviak Rook</span><br>  Posts: 370<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/31/01 9:38:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?to